            <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
            <br />
            <h5 id="q1">How do I order a Tesla vehicle?</h5>
            <p>Visit our Design Studio for Model 3 or Model Y to explore our latest options and place your order. The purchase price and estimated delivery date will change based on your vehicle design.</p>

            <h5 id="q2">Can I request a test drive?</h5>
            <p>Yes. You can request a test drive.<br>Note: Driver must be at least 25 years old with a minimum two years of driving experience and must hold a valid driver’s license.</p>

            <h5 id="q3">I have a question regarding my order. How do I get assistance?</h5>
            <p>You can contact us at <strong>Philippines@tesla.com</strong> or call us at <strong>+63-180013220087</strong>.</p>

            <h5 id="q4">I just designed my Tesla vehicle and submitted my order. What are the next steps?</h5>
            <p>As your delivery date approaches, we'll contact you to confirm your registration, payment method and additional information.</p>

            <h5 id="q5">Can I edit my design after placing my order?</h5>
            <p>After you have finalized your order, you cannot edit the design. Contact us if you have additional questions.</p>

            <h5 id="q6">If I place my order today, when can I expect to take delivery?</h5>
            <p>You can view the estimated delivery date in the Design Studio. The estimated delivery date depends on your vehicle design and is only an estimate. We will provide the specific timing of your delivery in your Tesla Account.</p>

            <h5 id="q7">Can I cancel my order?</h5>
            <p>Yes. Contact your Tesla Advisor.<br>Note: The order fee is non-refundable.</p>

            <h5 id="q8">What incentives are available when purchasing a Tesla vehicle?</h5>
            <p>You will be entitled to a 30% discount on the MVUC, priority vehicle registration with the LTO, and franchise processing with LTFRB. Electric vehicles are also exempted from vehicle volume reduction schemes like MMDA number coding.</p>

            <h5 id="q9">What is a Tesla Account?</h5>
            <p>Your Tesla Account includes owner resources, guides and updates. Additional details are made available as your delivery nears. Learn more about your Tesla Account.</p>

            <h5 id="q10">How can I prepare for delivery?</h5>
            <p>As your delivery date approaches, we'll contact you to confirm your registration, payment method and additional information.</p>

            <h5 id="q11">How do I get the Tesla app?</h5>
            <p>The Tesla app is available in the App Store (iOS) and Google Play (Android). Learn more about Tesla app features.</p>

            <h5 id="q12">Where will I take delivery of my vehicle?</h5>
            <p>We will provide the exact delivery location as the date nears.</p>

            <h5 id="q13">Does Tesla offer financing?</h5>
            <p>If you want to know more about financing solutions, contact your Tesla Advisor for details.</p>

            <h5 id="q14">Does Tesla have preferred insurance providers?</h5>
            <p>If you want to know more about insurance, contact your Tesla Advisor for more details.</p>

            <h5 id="q15">What are the local public charging options?</h5>
            <p>The Tesla Supercharger network is expanding and will be available soon in the Philippines. Supercharging is paid via your Tesla app. Idle fees may apply if your car is fully charged but still plugged in.</p>

            <h5 id="q16">What are the home charging options?</h5>
            <p>The most convenient way to charge your Tesla is at home, overnight. Install a Wall Connector for best results.</p>

            <h5 id="q17">What kind of warranty does my Tesla vehicle come with?</h5>
            <p>
                Your Tesla is covered by the New Vehicle Limited Warranty including:<br>
                - Basic Vehicle Limited Warranty<br>
                - SRS Limited Warranty<br>
                - Battery Limited Warranty
            </p>

            <h5 id="q18">What is Basic Vehicle Limited Warranty?</h5>
            <p>This covers repair or replacement of defective Tesla parts under normal use.</p>

            <h5 id="q19">What is SRS Limited Warranty?</h5>
            <p>This covers seat belts and air bag systems under normal use.</p>

            <h5 id="q20">What is Battery Limited Warranty?</h5>
            <p>This covers malfunctioning batteries and even damage from battery fires, with some exclusions.</p>
